<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jqa1665702719575.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jqa1665702719575.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jqa1665702719575.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jqa1665702719575\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set a path (or paths) used by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> ProcScript statement to be\n      asynchronous.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__topic_d139511e1_d139512e1_d139513e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__p_d139517e1_d139518e1_d139519e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$ASYNC_OPEN_UST=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UstName</var>{<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>...<var class=\"keyword varname\">UstName</var>\n            n }</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__section_gyg_4vt_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d342516e70\"> Arguments </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__p_d139523e1_d139524e1_d139525e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">UstName</var>—UST of a Uniface Server\n            for which a path is specified in the [PATHS] section of the client assignment file. The\n            UST must match exactly that one specified in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> statement. UST\n            names are case sensitive. Multiple USTs can be specified in a comma-separated list. No\n            spaces are allowed in the list.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__section_a54_4vt_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d342516e84\"> Defaults </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__table_d16532e1_d16533e1_d16534e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> client assignment file </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> [SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__section_e2s_4vt_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d342516e130\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jqa1665702719575__p_d139532e1_d139533e1_d139534e1\">By default, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span> ProcScript\n            statement uses a synchronous connection. This setting enables you to set the connections\n            for specified paths to be asynchronous when used by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">open</span>\n            command.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528990\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528990\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$ASYNC_OPEN_UST Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set a path (or paths) used by the open ProcScript statement to be asynchronous. $ASYNC_OPEN_UST= UstName { , ... UstName n } Arguments UstName —UST of a Uniface Server for which a path is specified in the [PATHS] section of the client assignment file. The UST must match exactly that one specified in the open statement. UST names are case sensitive. Multiple USTs can be specified in a comma-separated list. No spaces are allowed in the list. Defaults Assignment file: client assignment file Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description By default, the open ProcScript statement uses a synchronous connection. This setting enables you to set the connections for specified paths to be asynchronous when used by the open command. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}